1. Scope
This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use the App. By using the App, you agree to this Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the App.

2. Information we process
2.1 Content you create (stored on your device)
The App lets you create drawings and related content (“Artwork”). Artwork, thumbnails, titles/descriptions you enter, and editor state are stored locally on your device using on-device storage (for example, a local database and files on your device). We do not operate user accounts in the App and we do not intentionally upload your Artwork to our servers as part of core App functionality.

2.2 Photos and media you choose
If you choose to set a background from your gallery, the App accesses photos/media you select through the system picker / permissions required by your Android version (for example, access to images). We use this only to let you import an image into the canvas as you instruct.

2.3 Sharing
If you use sharing features, Artwork may be transmitted via the sharing channel you choose (for example, another app or service you select). Those services have their own privacy practices.

2.4 Device and network data (for App functionality and ads)
To operate the App and show advertising, the App may process limited technical data such as:

Network connectivity status (for example, to understand whether the device is online for ads or related features).
Device/app technical information commonly processed by mobile apps and advertising SDKs (for example, device identifiers used for advertising, IP address, general device information, app version, diagnostic signals).
Depending on your device settings and the advertising partner’s practices, ads may use advertising identifiers and related technologies.

