The App uses Google Mobile Ads (AdMob) and may show formats such as banner and app open ads (and any other formats we enable from time to time). AdMob and its partners may collect and use information to show and measure ads, including as described in Google’s policies.

Google’s Privacy & Terms: https://policies.google.com/privacy
How Google uses information from sites or apps that use their services: https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites
You can manage certain ad-related settings on your device (for example, opt out of personalized ads in Android settings where available).

4. Permissions
The App may request permissions needed for its features (for example, internet, network state, and access to images for importing backgrounds). Some permissions or capabilities may also be present because they are required by third-party libraries (including advertising SDKs). The system permission prompts describe what access is requested at runtime where applicable.

5. Legal bases (EEA/UK users)
If applicable law requires a legal basis, we rely on:

Contract / steps prior to contract (providing the App you request).
Legitimate interests (for example, securing the App, basic analytics related to ads delivery where used, preventing abuse), balanced against your rights.
Consent where required (for example, certain permissions or optional processing).
6. Retention
On-device Artwork remains until you delete it within the App or delete the App / clear app data on your device.
Information processed by advertising partners is retained according to their policies.
7. Security
We use reasonable measures appropriate to the nature of the App. No method of storage or transmission is 100% secure.

